👉 This proves:

FTP transmits credentials in plaintext, making it vulnerable to packet sniffing.

🚨 4. SYN Flood Attack Analysis
📌 What is SYN Flood?

A Denial of Service (DoS) attack where attacker sends multiple SYN requests but never completes handshake.

⚙️ Simulate Attack (Kali Linux)
hping3 -S --flood -p 80 <target_ip>
🔍 Wireshark Filter for SYN Packets
tcp.flags.syn == 1 && tcp.flags.ack == 0
📊 Observation
Large number of SYN packets
No ACK response
Half-open connections

👉 Indicates:

Server resources are getting exhausted → DoS condition

📈 5. Key Findings
HTTP and FTP traffic can expose sensitive data if not encrypted
DNS queries reveal browsing activity
FTP credentials can be easily captured
SYN flood attack causes service disruption
🛡️ 6. Mitigation Techniques
Use HTTPS instead of HTTP
Replace FTP with SFTP/FTPS
Enable firewall rules & IDS/IPS
Configure SYN cookies to prevent SYN flood
Monitor traffic using SIEM tools
